# Code owners for turnkey-sdk-csharp.
#
# This file only ASSIGNS reviewers. It does not enforce anything on its own:
# review by a code owner becomes mandatory only when branch protection on
# `main` has `require_code_owner_reviews` enabled. That is a repository
# setting and cannot be changed from a pull request. See CLAUDE.md, which
# states that cryptography and wire-format changes require independent
# maintainer review — this file is the mechanism that makes that routable.
#
# Owners must be able to resolve: GitHub silently ignores an unknown team or
# user, which would leave the rule looking present but doing nothing.
# `@KyuzanInc/peak-developers` is the team that currently holds push access
# on this repository.

# Default owner for everything not matched more specifically below.
*                           @KyuzanInc/peak-developers

# Cryptographic implementation and the signed wire format. Changes here are
# the ones CLAUDE.md singles out for independent review.
/src/                       @KyuzanInc/peak-developers

# Compatibility and CI gate scripts. These are the controls that prove the
# port still matches the pinned upstream, so a change here can weaken every
# other guarantee in the repository.
/tools/                     @KyuzanInc/peak-developers

# Workflow definitions, action pins, and release automation.
/.github/workflows/         @KyuzanInc/peak-developers
/.github/pin-actions.txt    @KyuzanInc/peak-developers

# Vendored upstream sources and their checksum manifests. These are SHA-256
# pinned; a change here alters what "matches upstream" means.
/tests/UpstreamSources/     @KyuzanInc/peak-developers
